
Static methods are declared using Static modifier

    Used for operations that dont require any data from an instance of the class (FROM THIS)

    This keyword is current instance of class

    1. In static we CAN'T USE THIS

Should method be static

    1. Does it use any fields (instance variables) or instance methods (this.)
        2. Yes -> SHOULD BE INSTANCE METHOD
        2. No -> SHOULD BE STATIC METHOD



STATIC AND INSTANCE VARIABLES

 - Static variables known as static member variables

Not used often - used when reading user input
- Scanner declared as a static method
- Then all static methods can access scanner directly


